    "__edge_metadata_27" [label=<
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="0" CELLPADDING="4">
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><B><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">Prerequisite Edge Description</FONT></B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Description:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">Techniques for modeling logical entailment relations<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>between natural‑language statements, used to build<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>explanatory reasoning chains such as entailment trees.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Explanation:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">The claim relies on treating NL pre/post‑conditions as<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>entailments that can be composed analogously to Hoare<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>triples.</FONT></TD></TR>
