<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><B><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">Prerequisite Edge Description</FONT></B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Description:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">A neural scoring model that estimates the usefulness<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>of a deductive step for reaching the goal, trained on<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>EntailmentBank data and used to prioritize the<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>deductive fringe.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Explanation:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">ADGV uses Hᵈ to select the most promising deductive<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>expansions, which is essential for the bidirectional<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>search to remain focused.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">strength: strong, weak; depth: 1</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
>, shape=box, style="rounded,filled,dashed", color="gray60", fillcolor="#eef2f7", fontname="Helvetica", margin="0.04,0.03"];
