<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="0" CELLPADDING="4">
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><B><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">Prerequisite Edge Description</FONT></B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Description:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">Methods such as premise abduction, query expansion,<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>and fact decomposition have been proposed to guide<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>multi‑step retrieval and reasoning over knowledge<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>bases.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Explanation:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">The evaluation of planning strategies alongside the<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>taxonomy builds on these earlier methods, informing<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>how evidence conditions affect retrieval planning.</FONT></TD></TR>
