<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="0" CELLPADDING="4">
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><B><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">Prerequisite Edge Description</FONT></B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Description:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">A fine‑tuned T5‑3B model that maps two premise strings<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>to a conclusion string, trained on the EntailmentBank<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>dataset. It is used to generate forward inferences and<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>to recompute conclusions for validation.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Explanation:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">Deductive Agreement requires the ability to recompute<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>the conclusion from a premise and an abductively<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>generated hypothesis, which is provided by Sᵈ.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">strength: strong; depth: 1</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
>, shape=box, style="rounded,filled,dashed", color="gray60", fillcolor="#e8f4ea", fontname="Helvetica", margin="0.04,0.03"];
    "253244513.c4" -> "__edge_metadata_41" [dir=none, weight=3];
    "__edge_metadata_41" -> "246015349.c0" [weight=3];
    "__edge_metadata_42" [label=<
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="0" CELLPADDING="4">
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><B><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">Prerequisite Edge Description</FONT></B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Description:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">A pretrained language model (based on the Bostrom et<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>al. 2022 implementation) fine‑tuned to map two<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>premises to a valid conclusion, used for forward<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>chaining in ADGV.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Explanation:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">Forms the forward generation component of ADGV; its<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>quality impacts the reported deductive‑agreement<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>scores and overall coverage.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">strength: strong; depth: 1</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
>, shape=box, style="rounded,filled,dashed", color="gray60", fillcolor="#e8f4ea", fontname="Helvetica", margin="0.04,0.03"];
    "253244513.c7" -> "__edge_metadata_42" [dir=none, weight=3];
    "__edge_metadata_42" -> "246015349.c0" [weight=3];
    "__edge_metadata_43" [label=<
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="0" CELLPADDING="4">
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><B><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">Prerequisite Edge Description</FONT></B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Description:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">Earlier works such as ProofWriter, Picco et al., and<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>Bostrom introduced the idea of iteratively applying a<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>neural model for single‑step inference and chaining<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>the results to produce multi‑step proofs for logical<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>reasoning.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Explanation:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">The current pipeline builds directly on this paradigm,<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>adapting its core idea to a minimalist implementation<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>and extending it to richer FOL constructs.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">strength: strong; depth: 1</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
>, shape=box, style="rounded,filled,dashed", color="gray60", fillcolor="#e8f4ea", fontname="Helvetica", margin="0.04,0.03"];
    "259858919.c1" -> "__edge_metadata_43" [dir=none, weight=3];
    "__edge_metadata_43" -> "246015349.c0" [weight=3];
    "__edge_metadata_44" [label=<
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="0" CELLPADDING="4">
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><B><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">Prerequisite Edge Description</FONT></B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Description:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">A modular system that generates candidate deductions<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>from premise pairs using a language model P(d | p₁,p₂)<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>and validates them with an entailment classifier,<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>constructing an entailment tree through iterative<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>expansion.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Explanation:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">Algorithm 1 iteratively calls this step model to<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>produce new deductions, making it essential for the<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>overall search procedure.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">strength: strong; depth: 1</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
>, shape=box, style="rounded,filled,dashed", color="gray60", fillcolor="#e8f4ea", fontname="Helvetica", margin="0.04,0.03"];
    "259343907.c1" -> "__edge_metadata_44" [dir=none, weight=3];
    "__edge_metadata_44" -> "246015349.c0" [weight=3];
    "__edge_metadata_45" [label=<
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="0" CELLPADDING="4">
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><B><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">Prerequisite Edge Description</FONT></B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Description:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">Earlier stepwise methods such as ProofWriter, FaiRR,<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>and SCSearch either banned hypothesis access or<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>generated steps greedily without verification, leading<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>to hallucinated or irrelevant steps.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Explanation:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">NLProofS builds on the insight that conditioning on<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>the hypothesis improves relevance but requires a<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>verifier to avoid hallucination, a problem identified<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>in these prior works.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">strength: strong; depth: 1</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
>, shape=box, style="rounded,filled,dashed", color="gray60", fillcolor="#e8f4ea", fontname="Helvetica", margin="0.04,0.03"];
    "249062748.c0" -> "__edge_metadata_45" [dir=none, weight=3];
    "__edge_metadata_45" -> "246015349.c0" [weight=3];
    "__edge_metadata_46" [label=<
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="0" CELLPADDING="4">
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><B><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">Prerequisite Edge Description</FONT></B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Description:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">A technique where generated proof steps are checked by<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>an independent model to ensure logical consistency,<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>previously used in NLProofs and related works.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Explanation:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">The cross‑verification step in FRVA directly adopts<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>this idea, requiring a verifier that can score both<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>deductive and abductive steps.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">strength: strong; depth: 2</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
>, shape=box, style="rounded,filled,dashed", color="gray60", fillcolor="#e8f4ea", fontname="Helvetica", margin="0.04,0.03"];
    "271931406.c2" -> "__edge_metadata_46" [dir=none, weight=3];
    "__edge_metadata_46" -> "249062748.c0" [weight=3];
    "__edge_metadata_47" [label=<
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="0" CELLPADDING="4">
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><B><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">Prerequisite Edge Description</FONT></B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Description:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">A prior method that uses an independent verifier to<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>guide stepwise proof generation and tree search (Yang<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>et al., 2022).</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Explanation:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">The alignment‑and‑fusion algorithm builds on the idea<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>of using verifier scores to prune and select proof<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>steps.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">strength: strong; depth: 2</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
>, shape=box, style="rounded,filled,dashed", color="gray60", fillcolor="#e8f4ea", fontname="Helvetica", margin="0.04,0.03"];
    "271931406.c4" -> "__edge_metadata_47" [dir=none, weight=3];
    "__edge_metadata_47" -> "249062748.c0" [weight=3];
    "__edge_metadata_48" [label=<
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="0" CELLPADDING="4">
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><B><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">Prerequisite Edge Description</FONT></B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Description:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">Existing systems for structured explanation, including<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>direct generation (EntailmentWriter) and stepwise<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>methods (RLET, IRGR, MetGen, NLProofs, FLD).</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Explanation:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">Performance of FRVA is measured against these<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>baselines to demonstrate improvements.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">strength: strong; depth: 2</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
>, shape=box, style="rounded,filled,dashed", color="gray60", fillcolor="#e8f4ea", fontname="Helvetica", margin="0.04,0.03"];
    "271931406.c5" -> "__edge_metadata_48" [dir=none, weight=3];
    "__edge_metadata_48" -> "249062748.c0" [weight=3];
    "__edge_metadata_49" [label=<
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="0" CELLPADDING="4">
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><B><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">Prerequisite Edge Description</FONT></B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Description:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">A three‑stage proof‑generation system that first<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>generates candidate steps, then searches over them,<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>and finally verifies each step with a trained verifier<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>model.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Explanation:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">The runtime of NLProofs (both with and without<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>verification) serves as the comparative baseline,<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>making it a core prerequisite for the analysis.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">strength: strong; depth: 2</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
>, shape=box, style="rounded,filled,dashed", color="gray60", fillcolor="#e8f4ea", fontname="Helvetica", margin="0.04,0.03"];
    "265150088.c3" -> "__edge_metadata_49" [dir=none, weight=3];
    "__edge_metadata_49" -> "249062748.c0" [weight=3];
    "__edge_metadata_50" [label=<
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="0" CELLPADDING="4">
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><B><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">Prerequisite Edge Description</FONT></B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Description:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">Techniques that greedily solve all equations until the<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>target is reached, exemplified by Proofwriter,<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>internal‑monologue, and verifier‑guided search<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>approaches, which inspire the exhaustive‑chaining<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>dimension.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Explanation:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">The exhaustive‑chaining strategy in the framework is<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>modelled after these prior exhaustive search methods.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">strength: strong; depth: 2</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
>, shape=box, style="rounded,filled,dashed", color="gray60", fillcolor="#e8f4ea", fontname="Helvetica", margin="0.04,0.03"];
    "256901153.c0" -> "__edge_metadata_50" [dir=none, weight=3];
    "__edge_metadata_50" -> "249062748.c0" [weight=3];
    "__edge_metadata_51" [label=<
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="0" CELLPADDING="4">
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><B><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">Prerequisite Edge Description</FONT></B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Description:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">Existing neural approaches that perform<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>forward‑chaining or backward‑chaining over<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>natural‑language rules, which cannot guarantee<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>derivation of all provable conclusions.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Explanation:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">GFaiR is motivated by the limitations of these methods<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>and seeks to overcome their incompleteness by using<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>resolution refutation.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">strength: strong; depth: 2</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
>, shape=box, style="rounded,filled,dashed", color="gray60", fillcolor="#e8f4ea", fontname="Helvetica", margin="0.04,0.03"];
    "268857317.c0" -> "__edge_metadata_51" [dir=none, weight=3];
    "__edge_metadata_51" -> "249062748.c0" [weight=3];
    "__edge_metadata_52" [label=<
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="0" CELLPADDING="4">
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><B><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">Prerequisite Edge Description</FONT></B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Description:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">The concept of constructing a tree of premises,<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>intermediate conclusions, and a hypothesis to explain<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>reasoning, originally introduced in the EntailmentBank<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>dataset and subsequent entailment‑tree generation<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>work.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="9" COLOR="gray35"><B>Explanation:</B></FONT><BR ALIGN="LEFT"/><FONT POINT-SIZE="9">The joint formulation directly adopts this paradigm to<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>structure multimodal evidence, so the underlying<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>theory and prior methods for entailment‑tree<BR ALIGN="LEFT"/>generation are required.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT POINT-SIZE="10">strength: strong; depth: 0</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
>, shape=box, style="rounded,filled,dashed", color="gray60", fillcolor="#e8f4ea", fontname="Helvetica", margin="0.04,0.03"];
